comments.body:
Thanks [~hex108] for the patch.
I think we can reuse RMAppAttempt object used for getting master container in {{getAmRPCAddressFromRMApp}} instead of getting current attempt again.
Moreover in getAmRPCAddressFromRMApp, we can store host and RPC port in a local variable or move this logic of generating AM RPC address to RMAppAttemptImpl and put it inside read lock. Reason being that in code below, host and rpc port may change between check for N/A and -1 and populating amRPCAddress if attempt fails in between. This may lead to an inconsistent response back to client.
{code}
if (attempt != null && !"N/A".equals(attempt.getHost())
        && attempt.getRpcPort() != -1) {
      amRPCAddress = attempt.getHost() + ":" + attempt.getRpcPort();
    }
{code}
